==English==
===Noun===
'''grand mal''' 

Etymology: from the French for Great Illness.

#A form of [[epilepsy]] where the [[seizure]]s are characterized as severe and involve [[spasm]]s and [[unconsciousness]].  A formal medical term would be Tonic-clonic seizures 

*Contrast [[petit mal]] seizures.

